My favorite chest exercises to do 👇

1️⃣ Smith Incline Bench Press: this exercise will work your upper chest.

2️⃣ Chest Dips: This exercise is great for your lower chest as well as your triceps 

3️⃣ Cable Flies: Great isolation exercise for the chest. Focus on squeezing and trying to bring your elbows together 

#fitness #gym #explore #viral #modeling #explorepage #bodybuilding #aesthetic #fitnessmotivation #fitnessmodel #gymrat #gymreels #abs #ejercicio

These exercises will give you that V shape look 👇

1️⃣ Pull-ups: This exercise will pretty much work your entire back. Depending on how you perform it, you can target more for width or thickness of the back 

2️⃣ Lateral Raises: This exercise will help build your side delts which is a lagging body part for most. This plus pull-ups will give you that V-shape look. 

3️⃣ Smith Incline Bench Press: This exercise will work your upper chest as well as your front delt. 

#fitness #gym #explore  #explorepage #bodybuilding #aesthetic #fitnessmotivation #gymrat #gymreels #ejercicio

📝 You can actually eat any food you like. As long as you are in a calorie deficit, you will lose weight. These are just some carbs I stick to during a cut !

1️⃣ Potatoes: They fill you up and have less calories compared to white rice. 

2️⃣ Fruit : Great way to get your micronutrients. They are a great snack to have that will keep you full for some time.

3️⃣ Tortillas: Make sure to buy the ones that don’t have a lot of extra calories. I stick to the ones that are 90-100 calories every TWO tortillas.

3 things you need to start doing to lose fat 👇

1️⃣ Increase activity level. The more we move the calories we burn and the more our metabolism works. This can be simple as aiming for 7K steps a day

2️⃣ Lift weights 3-5x a week. You don’t need to be in the gym more than hour to get in a good workout. By working out we will turn that fat into muscle 💪🏻 

3️⃣ Start tracking your calories. If you don’t know how many calories to eat, look up TDEE calculator online.
